olive oil
1 packet diced bacon
1 carrot
1 tin sweetcorn
1 sachet Garlic & Herb Seasoning
1 egg
1 tomato
2 radish
1 drizzle white wine vinegar
1 bag salad leaves
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese
¼ cup plain flour
1 packet Hollandaise
¼ tsp salt

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat.
Cook diced bacon, breaking up with a spoon, until golden, 4-5 minutes.
• Meanwhile, grate carrot. Squeeze out any excess moisture from carrot using
paper towel or clean cloth. Drain the sweetcorn.
• In a medium bowl, combine bacon, sweetcorn, carrot, grated Parmesan
cheese, garlic & herb seasoning, the egg and the plain flour. Add the salt
and a pinch of pepper, then mix well to combine.

TIP: Lift out some of the fritter mixture with a spoon. If it's too wet and doesn't
hold its shape, add a little more flour!

• Heat a large frying pan over medium-high heat with enough olive oil to coat
the base.
• When oil is hot, add heaped tablespoons of fritter mixture in batches and
flatten with a spatula.
• Cook fritters until golden, 3-4 minutes each side (don't flip too early!).
• Transfer to a paper towel-lined plate. You should get 3-4 fritters per person.
TIP: Add extra olive oil between batches as needed.

• Roughly chop tomato. Thinly slice radish.
• In a second medium bowl, combine a drizzle of white wine vinegar and
olive oil.
• Season, then add salad leaves, tomato and radish. Toss to combine.

• Divide bacon and Parmesan fritters between plates.
• Serve with radish salad and Hollandaise. Enjoy!